	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)">H.E.S&#39;s Rooms.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Feby 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1868</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev S. Morais</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My Dear Sir&#45;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Accompanying<lb/> please find the &#8220;resolutions&#8221;<lb/> I should wish to have made<lb/> them more elaborate but<lb/> time and the school prevented.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Do not hesitate to make<lb/> any change in them which<lb/> may seem advisable</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Yrs very truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">W. H. Williams</persName>.</p>
				<p>P.S.</p>
				<p>I showed them to <persName>Rev Mrss Beltteheim</persName><lb/> and <persName>Buttenwefin<add>&#63;</add></persName> they approve of them<lb/> but <persName>Mr Beltteheim</persName> suggests there<lb/> should be more recognition of his<lb/> position as <hi rend="underline">Provost</hi>&#61;</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>at a special meeting of the Faculty of Maimonides College held<lb/> in consequence of the sad bereavement recently <del>lately</del> sustained by<lb/> the house of <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; the following preamble and resolutions were<lb/> unanimously adopted</p>
				<p>Whereas the demise of the <persName>Revd Isaac Leeser</persName> is deemed by<lb/> each of us a national loss&#44; and whereas it is our conviction<lb/> that the establishing of this institution was principally due<lb/> to the unremitting exertions of our late colaborer&#44; and to his<lb/> constant advocacy of religious education&#44; <sic>therefre</sic></p>
				<p>Resolved that we express our feelings of deep sorrow at the<lb/> loss of a man so zealous for the moral welfare of his people&#44;<lb/> so energetic in promoting the culture of human knowledge&#44; so<lb/> efficient as a professor&#44; so exemplary assiduous in the discharge<lb/> of <add>all</add> his duties.</p>
				<p>Resolved that we <del>gladly</del> <add>&#63;</add> bearing our testimony to the unborn<add>&#63;</add> kindness and<lb/> courtesy that marked his official relations with us&#44; and to<lb/> his timely and useful suggestions as <del>the</del> Provost of this College</p>
				<p>Resolved that we will <add>ever</add> cherish his memory as that of a friend&#44;<lb/> and teach <del>our</del> the students of this institution to revere his <del>memory</del> name</p>
				<p>Resolved that these resolutions be published in all Jewish <add>one of our dailies</add><lb/> periodicals&#59; <del>and</del></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">S. Morais</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Sect Pt.</p>
				<p><date>February 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1868</date></p>
		</body>
